# CODEOWNERS — review request routing for critical files
#
# GitHub automatically requests a review from the listed owner when these paths
# change in a PR. This is a routing signal, not a merge gate — branch protection
# does not require Code Owner approval (solo developer, ADR-018).
# The governance constraint is: agents must not commit changes to these paths
# without explicit human instruction. See AGENTS.md and ADR-020.
# Reference: docs/adr/ADR-017-extended-toolchain.md, ADR-018, ADR-020

# Cryptographic implementation — any change here is a security decision
/crates/arcanum-crypto/         @umudique
/crates/arcanum-pqc/            @umudique

# Protocol and cryptographic specifications — source of truth
/specs/                         @umudique

# Architecture decisions — immutable without explicit human approval
/docs/adr/                      @umudique

# Supply chain and policy configuration
/deny.toml                      @umudique
/Cargo.toml                     @umudique
/rust-toolchain.toml            @umudique

# CI and security scanning pipelines
/.github/workflows/             @umudique
/.github/CODEOWNERS             @umudique

# Agent instruction and governance files
/AGENTS.md                      @umudique
/docs/agents/                   @umudique
/docs/security/                 @umudique
